parameters: \n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>*Puff*\.\. Welcome to the \c[18]Fishing Web Aquarium\c[0]!\.\.
O-Rin lets out a big puff of smoke.\.\.
She hums,\. eying Neneko's collection,\. the creatures inside the tank mingling about peacefully in their strangeness.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>Hm hm...\.\.\. you're keeping busy,\. aren't you?\.\.
She looks amused,\. a glint in her eyes,\. each of them.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>Seems like you can be a hard worker when you want to be.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>Appearances are deceiving...\.\.\. I wasn't expecting this much diligence.\.\. Good work,\. Neko.\.\.
O-Rin gives another hum,\. tilting her head thoughtfully.\.\. She puffs out another ball of smoke,\. causing Neneko to hiss and wave her hand in front of her.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>Oh?\.\. What's wrong?\.\. You don't seem particularly pleased.\.\. I figured you were the boisterous type.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>Is my praise not good enough for you?\.\.
\n<\n[1]>I mean,\. don't get me wrong,\. all of this is easy for me.\.\. I've got plenty of experience hunting down critters,\. yeah.\.\.
Neneko groans,\. waving her hands at the aquarium.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Look at those things!\.\. Aren't they...\.\.\. I dunno,\. weird?\.\.
The spiderlike woman brings her pipe to her mouth,\. inhaling slowly before leaning back.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>Weird how,\. Neko-\.san?\.\. You will have to be a bit more specific for me.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Ugh...\.\.\. just,\. like...\.\.\. I've seen plenty of fish,\. I know my fish!\.\. I love fish!\.\.
\n<\n[1]>But these...\.\.\. these aren't fish!\.\. They don't look tasty at all!\.\. \BST[3]I don't think even cooking them will make them any better!\.\.
Neneko crosses her arms,\. grumbling as she bends down to stare into the aquarium.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>...\.\.\. Haaa...\.\.\. were you expecting to eat your collection once we were done recording them,\. Neko-\.san?\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>...\.\.\. Let me ask you.\.\. Where do you think we are?\.\.
O-Rin looks up,\. a thoughtful expression on her face,\. her pipe swaying in her hand.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>Let's throw out a random number.\.\. I'd say we are...\.\.\. let's say,\. 2000 meters below the town on the surface.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>All the water here comes down from above in rivers or streams or waterfalls.\.\. It's a long,\. long way down.\.\. Only the sturdiest fish can survive the trip...\.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>And then,\. when they get here...\.\.\. the ecology can't sustain them at all.\.\. The plants are different.\.\. The climate is strange.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>And that is ignoring the Mana soaking everything down here.\.\.
O-Rin looks to Neneko,\. waving her pipe.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>So,\. if you were a fish and suddenly fell down here,\. you now have three options,\. you see.\.\. \BST[1]Do you know what those are,\. Neko?\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>It's simple.\.\. One-\. You can die of hunger and exposure.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>Two-\. You can die from mana poisoning.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>Or Three...\.\.\. you can change yourself to be able to survive in a place like this.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>So...\.\.\. the fish down here,\. what,\. mutated from the magic?\.\.
O-Rin looks down at the aquarium,\. peering at the strange critters within.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>You won't see any normal bugs and fish down here,\. Neko.\.\. \BST[3]Frankly speaking...\.\.\. even the wildlife on the First Stratum I'd hesitate to call insects or fish.\.\.

\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>They've become closer to "monsters".\.\. Beings of Mana.\.\. I doubt even if you tried to eat them they wouldn't have much nutritional value,\.\BST[3] let alone taste good.\.\.
\n<\n[1]>Ugh...\.\.\. you're making me lose my appetite...\.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>Sadly it's the truth,\. love.\.\.
O-Rin huffs,\. standing up straight and turning to face Neneko.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>You won't be getting any fine cuisine down here.\.\. Not by fishing,\. at least.\.\.
O-Rin chuckles as Neneko reels back in despair.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>Most of the food supplies for the people at this level are delivered from up above and straight to the dwarves' fortress.\.\. Including the fish.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>And they charge a lot of money for the delivery.\.\. \BST[2]Any normal meat at all is a luxury,\. really.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>Haaa...\.\.\. come,\. now.\.\. Did you think you were on some fun camping trip?\.\.
O-Rin stares at Neneko,\. judgemental,\. unimpressed.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>This place isn't kind.\.\. It isn't fun.\.\. Quite frankly,\. it's hell.\.\. \BST[3]I am lucky to only be on the first Stratum.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>If you cannot handle this wild wasteland of a death pit,\. then...\.\.\.
She leans forward,\. blowing smoke in Neneko's face as she exhales deeply.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>Go back up to the Surface.\.\. Find a cozy little tree to take a catnap under,\. and then have all the fat,\. juicy fish you want up there.\.\.
They stare each other down,\. before O-Rin smirks,\. leaning back.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>Come back around when you have more for the records,\. Neko-\.san.\.\. Maybe I'll share a drink with you when you bring an impressive haul.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>You...\.\.\. you're not from the Fortress.\.\. A new face?\.\. A diver?
\n<\N[1]>...\.\.\. *cough*\.\. That's none of your business,\. stinky...
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>You're from the Surface,\. aren't you?\.\. An illegal maybe?
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>I don't really care...\.\.\. Have you met my little sister above ground?\.\. I hope she's fine...
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>Have you met my little sister above ground?\.\. I hope she's fine...

\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>I'm not into fish myself,\. but I've promised my sisters to do my job here,\. so...\.\.\.
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>It's nice looking at them swim in the tank...\.\.\. peaceful...\.\.\. unaware...
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>Now I have to take a picture of your fish...\.\.\. Hmm,\. I'm not that good with this thing...
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>Let's try...\.\.\. should I push here or...?
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>!\.\. That worked...\.\.\. not too shabby,\. huh?
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>Another \ii[\v[218]]?\.\. Can't you catch anything new for our tank!?\.\. My sisters are gonna bother me...
\n<Fishing Sister O-Rin>But I guess I should compliment you anyway...
"1.\.\. At all times, make sure there's no more than 5 fishes in the tank."
"2.\.\. Clean the tank and change the water regularly. Water from the Lake is advised."
"3.\.\. Be mindful of the species there's in the tank. Similarly sized fishes are less likely to snack on each other!"
